				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Thinking about getting back into EQ<a name="18579"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 2 04 6:24 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I used to play a druid prior to Luclin coming out for about a year or so and then I quit because my computer did not run eq very well (it took me about 3 minutes to go from one zone to another<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-9.gif" border="0" alt="Crying" hspace="2" />) so I quit because I spent more time wiaitng for my computer to load the next zone then actual hunting (since I was hunting in the Overthere and Dragoons were constant so often had to runt to the zone.)  Anyway, recently I got a faster computer and I had a Free EQ Trial for 15 days (although for some reason it only gave me 5<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />) and was able to play again for a short time.  Anyway, i've liked how the game has changed since I last played and i'm looking forwar to playing some kind of MMORPG in the future (either this or FFXI since WoW won't be out for a while, even if Blizzard announces a release date<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />)  Anyway, I decided that I might want to get back into EQ since I already somewhat know how to play the game already and i'd rather not learn a completely different game alltogether right now since i'd rather just play.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, i've been a lurker here for the pas week or so and I am pretty sure I have a pretty good idea on how to play a bard very well and effectively for myself(solo if I do) and group.  My question is, if I were to get back into EQ are there any server recommendations out there?  I used to play on The Rathe but I didn't find it very enjoyable since most people outcasted me from groups since I was a very poor druid (I couldn't become a taxi or whatever it was called since it took too long to zone once Luclin was emerging) and I was barely getting by each spell sets, usually not being able to buy useful ones until I had money but I had access to the next set<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-9.gif" border="0" alt="Crying" hspace="2" /> so most groups did not want me since I was in my low 40's (I think I was level 42 or so) in my newbie armor (from Crushbone, yes Crushbone) with maybe 1/2 or 3/4 of his spells.  Anyway, I've been reading up about FV but decided it wouldn't be my cup of tea since i'd like to make other characters and I wouldn't exactly like deleting my character in favor of a new one.  Anyway, on my trial i've been playing on Tunare and it wasn't bad but I found the people(at least in Crushbone/Gfay/BB) very mean/rude or at least when I played (although there were a few people nice that gave me a Dwarven Ringmail Tunic when I didn't ask <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />.  Anyway, just looking for somewhere to go as I hope to get into 50+ and try to experience supposedly what most people have not experienced in the game before.
<br />

<br />
Also, i've been reading about other characters, can someone explain to me what AA's are?  I'm really confused on how they're obtained and what they do exactly.  Augments too, I have no idea what these are and i'm drawing a blank when I try to think about it.  Oh yeah, when I want to BB from the Gfay zone, why is there a big group of people just standing in this one spot?  I thought it might be a guild meeting or something but when I through there a couple of other times, still a large group remained, was this just a fluke of some sort because I didn't exactly go in since I thought they'd be angry if I was interrupting a guild meeting or something.  Very long read, but if anyone can answer parts if not all of my post, i'd greatly apreciate it.
<br />

<br />
Nameless Future bard(haven't decided a name yet)
<br />
No home yet (since I haven't decided on what server to start)</span></td>
