				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Thinking about getting back into EQ<a name="18654"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 3 04 8:20 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'll have a go at answering some of your questions.  AA is Alternate Advancement.  It allows you to put all or a portion of your experience into these points instead of just leveling after you reach level 50.  The hoards you see in Butcherblock are at one of the wayfarer camps that were added with the Lost Dungeon's of Norrath expansion.  Augs are augmentation gems that drop in the LDoN adventures.  They can be applied to weapons or armor to add stats or resists.  It's a way to improve some of the older bits in the game, particularly the ones that have sentimental valur to you.
<br />

<br />
I think I'm going to dodge the server question.  I will, however, make one observation.  The older the server, the more likely that low level characters are to be an alt of someone that has been playing the game for a long time and not a complete newbie to the game.  Thus, people seem to be less likely to cut you some slack for being low level.  This is especially true if their main happens to be the class you are playing.  I don't know what, if any, the solution to this is.  Just keep playing and do the best you can.
<br />

<br />
Good luck to you.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
