				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Thinking about getting back into EQ<a name="18726"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 3 04 11:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Consider coming to Firiona Vie, and consider Molto Espressivo.  We are an all bard guild that was born on the old eqdiva message boards about a year ago.  Kocho just made us a forum here, but we have not really migrated here yet from the old ezboards.  
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://pub142.ezboard.com/feqdivabardsofeverquestfrm83">http://pub142.ezboard.com/feqdivabardsofeverquestfrm83</a>
<br />

<br />
FV is indeed a better place to bring up a newbie than most other servers.  There is a generally more mature player base there, and many that are more concerned with experiencing the game than racing to 65 etc.  Thus, newbie zones are not deserted, and you can actually get a group.
<br />

<br />
The fact that almost nothing is no-drop means that you can buy lots of cool stuff with plat.  That does also make FV the Ebayers server of choice, cause you can just charge it all to your credit card etc...  Don't let that dissuade you though.  Between that, and the recent plat-duping thing that they finally cracked down on, very high end gear is crazy expensive.  Prices are already dropping though.
<br />

<br />
If you join Molto, you will have the added benefit of our hand-me-down gear, and our smiths who are working on skillups, hehe.  We don't sell our gear to finance upgrades.  We pass all our stuff on to lower level bards.
<br />

<br />
Scherzo Glissando
<br />
Troubador of 55 Compositions
<br />
Maestro, Molto Espressivo
<br />
Firiona Vie</span></td>
